  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OSTINATO — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Chauvet Cave (32,000 BCE): the oldest musical instrument is the cave itself — its resonant chambers were chosen by Paleolithic humans specifically for drumming ceremonies",
      "Iamblichus: 'The cave is the image of the universe — the world is a cave, and the philosopher learns by going down before going up'",
      "Australian Aboriginal teaching: 'The Dreaming does not happen in time — it happens in place. The cave is where time stops and the Dreaming begins'"
    ],
    "revelation": "Eye revealed: Cave bodyModel with high body (0.85+) and high exciterMix creates a 'stone resonator' character — the drum disappears and what remains is the acoustic shape of a hollow space. At circleAmount=0.45 with 6 cave-bodied instruments, the sympathetic resonance sounds like the cave has become conscious.",
    "god": "Eye",
    "flock_note": "The Feather insisted: reverbDamp=0.7 is key — undamped reverb on Cave body creates a muddy accumulation. The dampening creates the impression of a REAL cave with absorptive surfaces (moss, earth, bodies) rather than a stone echo chamber. The result is intimate rather than cavernous.",
    "diagnosis": "Cave Ceremony returns percussion to its oldest context — not performance, not entertainment, but the activation of a resonant space that already knew how to sing."
  },
